{"parse":{"title":"The Life and Times of Conrad Black","pageid":47012246,"revid":818497653,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><p><i><b>The Life and Times of Conrad Black</b></i> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wordless_novel\" title=\"Wordless novel\">wordless novel</a> by Canadian artist <a href=\"/wiki/George_Walker_(printmaker)\" title=\"George Walker (printmaker)\">George Walker</a>, published in 2013.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Conrad_Black_mug_shot.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Conrad_Black_mug_shot.jpg/220px-Conrad_Black_mug_shot.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"271\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Conrad_Black_mug_shot.jpg/330px-Conrad_Black_mug_shot.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Conrad_Black_mug_shot.jpg/440px-Conrad_Black_mug_shot.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"650\" data-file-height=\"800\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Conrad_Black_mug_shot.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/wiki/Conrad_Black\" title=\"Conrad Black\">Conrad Black</a>'s mug shot in 2005</div></div></div>\n<p>Walker's followed up his first wordless novel, <i>The Mysterious Death of Tom Thomson</i> (2012) about the death of <a href=\"/wiki/Tom_Thomson\" title=\"Tom Thomson\">the well-known Canadian painter</a>, with a biography of the media mogul <a href=\"/wiki/Conrad_Black\" title=\"Conrad Black\">Conrad Black</a>.  Walker stated his motivation was that Black was \"one of the most outspoken and charismatic characters in the elusive one per cent of people who make up the establishment in Canada.  He is a public person of international stature, at one time a media baron and still a man of great influence and wealth.\"  Black approved of the book, and signed a few copies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTERavvin2014_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTERavvin2014-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  Black is the author of numerous books and newspaper articles and has a reputation for the verbosity of his prose.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHeer2013_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEHeer2013-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>100 wordless black-and-white <a href=\"/wiki/Woodcut\" title=\"Woodcut\">woodcut</a> prints make up the book telling Black's life story.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHeer2013_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEHeer2013-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  Walker based the images on photographs, many from newspapers or magazines and familiar to the public.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEPostema201592\u201393_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEPostema201592\u201393-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>  He communicated with Black via email while Black was in prison in Florida; Black reviewed the woodcut images, rejecting some he felt were too controversial and making suggestions for others.  Walker hand-printed the first edition of the book in a limited boxed edition of 13 copies, symbolic of the thirteen boxes Black removed from his office when it was investigated in 2005.  Each copy was signed by Black and priced at $1,500.  A popular edition later appeared from Porcupine's Quill<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEEverett-Green2013_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEEverett-Green2013-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> in 2013.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEPostema201594_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEPostema201594-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:George_Walker_(printmaker).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Photograph of a bearded man in a brimmed hat\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/George_Walker_%28printmaker%29.jpg/220px-George_Walker_%28printmaker%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"330\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d5/George_Walker_%28printmaker%29.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"288\" data-file-height=\"432\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:George_Walker_(printmaker).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/wiki/George_Walker_(printmaker)\" title=\"George Walker (printmaker)\">George Walker</a></div></div></div>\n<p>Walker's choice of Black as a subject stands in contrast to wordless novel traditions, which normally focused on emotional working-class characters and socialist politics; Black is a wealthy capitalist who reins in his emotions in public.  Walker does not use the book to attack or belittle Black, but simply relates the mogul's story from his days at <a href=\"/wiki/Upper_Canada_College\" title=\"Upper Canada College\">Upper Canada College</a>\u2014where he was <a href=\"/wiki/Caning\" title=\"Caning\">caned</a>\u2014through his rise in the media, his arrest and imprisonment for fraud and obstruction of justice and release from prison.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHeer2013_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEHeer2013-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Life_and_Times_of_Conrad_Black&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 20em; -webkit-column-width: 20em; column-width: 20em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTERavvin2014-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTERavvin2014_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFRavvin2014\">Ravvin 2014</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEHeer2013-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHeer2013_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHeer2013_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHeer2013_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFHeer2013\">Heer 2013</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEPostema201592\u201393-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEPostema201592\u201393_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFPostema2015\">Postema 2015</a>, pp.&#160;92\u201393.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEEverett-Green2013-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEEverett-Green2013_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFEverett-Green2013\">Everett-Green 2013</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEPostema201594-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEPostema201594_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFPostema2015\">Postema 2015</a>, p.&#160;94.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Works_cited\">Works cited</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Life_and_Times_of_Conrad_Black&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Works cited\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r853264625\">.mw-parser-output .refbegin{font-size:90%;margin-bottom:0.5em}.mw-parser-output .refbegin-hanging-indents>ul{list-style-type:none;margin-left:0}.mw-parser-output .refbegin-hanging-indents>ul>li,.mw-parser-output .refbegin-hanging-indents>dl>dd{margin-left:0;padding-left:3.2em;text-indent:-3.2em;list-style:none}.mw-parser-output .refbegin-100{font-